backpack.title: Character Profile
backpack.titleText:
This strange world, the one that you now inhabit, has been forever changed.
This is an index page to the novel of your new life:

backpack.title: Passive
backpack.titleText:
You can't expect to come out unscathed after contact with the eldritch.
You observe new.. developments within your vessel.

backpack.title: Manifestation
backpack.titleText: The powers that goes beyond realms of Any understanding, But one cannot deny the awe and fear it inspires.

backpack.title: Evolution
backpack.titleText: Some Powers that are granted to you can be evolved beyond their initial description, This evolution brings out massive changes and boost in the powers provided, These only inspires fear.

backpack.title: Imperfections
backpack.titleText: Ofcourse, You wanted more power, More power doesn't come at a cheap price, The price is your sanity.

backpack.title: Sanity status
backpack.titleText: This is to check How much degradation, both mental and physical you underwent in your quest for power.

backpack.title: Anomalies
backpack.titleText: Eldritch power change more than just humanity, some places in world display bizarre behavior

backpack.title: Ascended ones
backpack.titleText: Ascended Ones were once human who got corrupted by the powers given to them, Now they are monsters dead set on killing every life they see.

backpack.title: Companions
backpack.titleText: Strength in numbers they say, Might as well put it to practice.

objects.title: Intro
objects.text: Ah. You're awake. Good. I was beginning to wonder if your brain had melted like Subject Thirty-Two. Footsteps. He.. or is it a She? Something steps into view Don’t worry. Your vitals are stable—surprisingly so. Guess our hypothesis was correct after all, You are compatible with the ESPER procedure! That level of compatibility is... unbelievably rare, you know? Most of our elite soldiers, genius scientists—failures. Their minds turned to soup. And yet, some random civilian plucked off the street passes with flying colors? She(?) smiles thinly, like it hurts to do so. You’ve been gifted—or cursed, depending on your outlook—with a unique compatibility to the... material. Alien in origin, psionic in nature. Most minds snap like twigs... Yours? He(?) leans closer. You feel the weight of his gaze. Yours didn’t. Yours adapted.

objects.title: Origin
objects.text: We're going to be here for a long time... might as well chat with you while I'm at it The figure goes back to working, fingers gliding across glowing tablets and unfamiliar machinery. You hear the hum of something alive. It all started 27 months ago. The meteor shower of January 2023. For most, it was just that— A pretty little cosmic phenomenon. We thought the same... at first. But those weren’t some space rocks... They were organic. Fragments of something—some being—shattered across the stars and crash-landed here. He flicks his fingers. Monitors around you flash, showing streaks of fire falling from the sky. The corpse—if you can call it that—still had active DNA. And when exposed to a compatible host, it fuses. Bonds. Awakens them to psychic powers. He Stares at you for a second too long We discovered it by accident. Some German researcher brushed against a sample. Next thing we know— His colleague was flambéed during lunch..

objects.title: Origin
objects.text: And to nobody’s surprise, we humans caught on very quickly. A new source of power? Naturally, we did what we do best— Started a war. He shrugs, still focused on his work—casual, like he’s commenting on the weather. Oh, not the usual kind. No grand invasions. No mushroom clouds. That’s bad PR these days. This was... quieter. Cleaner. A shadow war, waged by ghosts no one could trace. Espers... A new frontier in warfare. Of course, the only limiting factor... is compatibility. But when one body becomes a weapon of mass destruction? That little issue becomes very negotiable. He chuckles. The sound is dry, almost hollow. Then a picture appears—faces on a missing persons chart, dozens of them. So many people... vanished. You’ve seen the headlines, I’m sure. ‘Mass Disappearances.’ ‘Unsolved Cases.’ But science—real science—demands sacrifices. He steps closer. A scan hums around you, projecting faint symbols and pulses across the glass between you. Hmm… fascinating. Signs of awakening already. A bit slower than most—typical civilian neuroplasticity—but still… promising.

rows.title: Emotional Response
rows.titleText:
I need to gauge your emotional response to this Procedure as a whole, And calibrate all my readings and actions accordingly.
<i>So Tell me, How do you feel?<i>

objects.title: Resentment
objects.text:
You feel it rising in your chest—hot, suffocating rage.
This Thing tore you away from your life, from everything you knew, You NEVER ASKED FOR THIS.
<b> Your hands may be bound, but your hatred burns freely.<b>

objects.title: Acceptance
objects.text:
You don’t feel much at all. 
Just… numb.
You weren’t anyone important. No big dreams.. No nothing.
<i>Maybe this is better. Maybe now, at least, you have a purpose—even if you never asked for it.<i>

objects.title: Fear
objects.text:
You don’t understand any of this.
Aliens, DNA, psychic powers… it’s too much. Too fast.
You're Scared..
<b>All you want is to wake up and be in your bed, back home, where things made sense.<b>

rows.title: Location
rows.titleText:
Well I need to confirm if your brain can still function properly, say..
How does this facility looks like to you?

objects.title: Complex
objects.text: You glance through the thick observation glass lining the corridor walls. What you see defies logic—rooms stacked in impossible geometry, stairs leading nowhere, platforms that shift like clockwork mechanisms caught mid-turn. The layout seems to rearrange itself ever so slightly when you’re not looking directly at it. "Through the help of that alien DNA, we developed tech we could only dream of. A whole underground complex that can shift and adapt as we need. Self-sustaining. Self-repairing. Self-aware.. Even I get lost."

objects.title: Aqautic
objects.text: Beyond the Window lies a slow-drifting void of endless blue. Water presses in from all sides, thick and cold and infinite. You spot silhouettes of fish moving lazily in the distance. There's no land. No sunlight. Just the low hum of pressure systems and distant sonar pulses echoing through the abyss. "Ah, you noticed. We are underwater. The entire facility, floating among the ocean like some metallic leviathan. Self-contained. Pressure-sealed. Escape, I’m afraid, would require gills… or resurrection."

objects.title: Mountain
objects.text: You turn to a frosted window and peer through. Wind screams beyond the glass, and clouds billow past like smoke. Below, just barely visible, are jagged cliffs dusted with snow—and far, far beneath that, the outline of a treeline. There’s no city in sight. Just isolated wilderness and vertical death. "Cliffside Facility. 7500 meters above Sea level. The nearest human settlement is... well, irrelevant. You won’t be walking there. This height? This isolation? Perfect for secrecy. And any foolish attempt to leave would be... real foolish."

You blink. That can’t be right. Beyond the one-way glass lies what looks like a suburban neighborhood—quiet homes, empty streets, mailboxes lined neatly like little soldiers. There’s no one around, but everything seems oddly pristine… like a model town left mid-play. Nothing moves. Nothing breathes.. "Tch tch. Don’t be fooled. We currently exist in a separate dimension, stabilized by an ally nation's Esper. Pocket reality, you could call it. There is no exit. No people. Only you… and me."

rows.title: Passives
rows.titleText:
Eldritch energies course through your being, bringing with them a new set of "passive abilities" that manifest as side effects. These abilities are akin to ones you find in 'video games', Such amusing creation may I say.
These "passives" manifest as subtle advantages or unique traits that influence and complement your actions. They are not necessarily directly controllable by you, functioning like an extension of your being.
<b> Choose 3 to enforce upon yourself<b>

objects.title: Glamour
objects.text:
You can passively conceal the changes to your appearance, making others perceive you as you did before the mutations.
But this effect is not infallible and may collapse during moments of heightened emotions when your emotional control falters.

objects.title: Improved
objects.text:
Your natural senses have been heightened to an absurd degree.
You can see with heightened clarity in darkness, hear faint sounds from further away.
However, this heightened sensory perception comes without mental adjustments, so be prepared for over stimulation as your senses become supercharged.

objects.title: Unyielding
objects.text:
Your will is exceptionally strong, never wavering even in the face of adversity, Possessing an unbreakable spirit that refuses to give up, no matter how dire the circumstances.
This indomitable spirit, though, can occasionally make you overly stubborn, refusing to yield even when surrender might be the wiser move.

objects.title: Intellect
objects.text:
Your intellect has been amplified, increasing by 15-20 IQ points.
Your analytical skills sharper, making you capable of analyzing and solving complex problems with ease.
Though this enhanced intelligence can lead to a cold and rational approach, Leading you toward unethical choices in pursuit of efficiency and logic.

objects.title: Finesse
objects.text:
Your control over your powers has become more refined, allowing you to use them with greater precision and efficiency.
However, this precision also means you struggle to truly let loose, continuously holding back and restraining yourself from completely tapping into your potential.

objects.title: Warning
objects.text:
You possess a subtle, yet innate, sense that alerts you to the presence of eldritch entities.
This intuition manifests as a chilling sensation down your spine, a subconscious awareness of the presence.
However, it does not reveal details about the entity's affiliations, level of danger, or intentions.

objects.title: Disruption
objects.text:
Your emotions have ability to tap into the eldritch energies within you. 
Whenever you experience heightened emotions, your eldritch energies trigger disturbances in nearby electrical devices, causing lights to flicker and screens to glitch.
The greater your emotional intensity, the more potent the disruptions.

objects.title: Endurance
objects.text:
Your body has the ability to function continuously for extended periods of time without rest. 
It can sustain itself by harnessing ambient energies from the world around you.
This enables you to operate for a full month without requiring either food or water, yet still remain vigilant for your health.

objects.title: Reflex
objects.text:
Your reflexes have reached superhuman levels, allowing you to respond to stimuli that no human should be able to.
This enhancement is entirely subconscious, which means it can activate even in the face of minor threats, leading to problems such as over-reacting to insignificant events.

objects.title: Truth
objects.text:
You possess an uncanny ability to discern when someone is lying to you. When someone is intentionally untruthful, you hear a sharp, piercing ringing sound in your ears.
This ability, however, only activates when the speaker intends to speak directly to you. Audio recordings or indirect communication won't trigger the alarm.

objects.title: Manupilate
objects.text:
The Eldritch influence within you grants you an uncanny understanding of the desires and weaknesses of others, allowing you to manipulate and sway them effortlessly.
You have no qualms utilizing this passive to toy with people's emotions for your amusement, viewing them as mere playthings.

objects.title: Recall
objects.text:
Your memory has been fortified by eldritch influences, making it virtually impossible for you to forget. 
You now possess eidetic memory, ability to recall anything you have ever learned, with no memory degradation.
However, there may be certain memories you genuinely wish to forget.

rows.title: Companions
rows.titleText: In the new world you are thrust into, there is no hope for normalcy. Despair and darkness seem to engulf everything. Your enduring heart may keep you afloat, but it's within a group that true light can be found. While there are certainly those who bask in the power granted to them, there are also brave souls who resist the lure of the inner darkness. Along your journey, you are likely to cross paths with such individuals. You are encouraged to establish a support network with these like-minded individuals to overcome challenges and survive the apocalyptic circumstances together. Lean on each other's strengths and collaborate to fill the gaps, ensuring the collective well-being in this tumultuous time. I can give you a glimpse into their psyche, Manifesting their ideology and characteristics to help in the selection process. Choose 3 companions, 4 if you got the 'BFF' Complication

objects.title: Viroop
objects.text:
A fellow empowered individual with roots in the Indian subcontinent, Viroop asserts that he was thrown to this region by someone with portal-based abilities. Despite his seemingly ominous appearance, shaped by his remarkable mutation, he is an exceptionally kind and considerate individual. His primary concern is the needs of others before his own. Possessing complete mastery over his biological structure, Viroop is capable of transforming into any form he perceives and boasts some of the most potent regenerative abilities among the individuals mentioned in this listing. Psychosis:

Hi? I'm not quite sure how I ended up here, but I would love to assist in any way I can. I have been granted the gift to command my body and even change my appearance to match others. I wouldn't use this power to deceive or harm anyone, though. It feels wrong to me. I know I might not look 'nice,' but I assure you, I will not hurt anyone here. I promise.

addons.title: Status: Host
addons.text: - Skinwalker: Can rearrange biomass to copy any human look. - Animorph: Can assume form of Elephant, Swan, Rat, fish and Bear. - Undying: Can regenerate from even a handful of flesh in 15 mins. - Forge: Can induce minor mutations in his body, lasts for 3 minutes.

objects.title: Vanessa Emerald Crane
objects.text:
Vanessa E. Crane is a perplexing woman, her personal life a well-guarded mystery. She is always seen in mourning clothes, never revealing much about herself. She is consistently seen dressed in widow's attire, Curiously enough, she carries a human skull with her, adamantly claiming that she did not kill the person it belonged to. Despite her peculiar ways, Vanessa possesses exceptional telepathic powers, Her mental defenses are unmatched, preventing even me from glimpsing into her memories. However, through a few skillful moves, I managed to obtain an analysis of her mind. Psychosis:

Greetings. I sensed something probing my mind, but it wasn't you. Still, I must compliment the attempt. I like you, Your mind feels nice. I can't stand people with an irritating presence; I even avoid using my powers on them. Would you be my friend? I'm tired of being alone, but the thought of losing another scares me. Especially after what happened to... never mind.

addons.title: Status: Psion
addons.text: - Connect: Can connect to anyone within 142 meters and casually read thoughts, and even memories with effort. - Telekill: Is unaffected by attempts of telekinesis or mind alterations. - Blackout: Can shut down any mind that is weaker than her own.

objects.title: Orcus
objects.text:
Orcus, who identifies himself only by that name, is a young man in his late twenties with a soft, effeminate face and physique, often causing others to question his gender. His head is crowned with a peculiar horn mutation, giving a regal look. His cunning nature has been shaped by the betrayals he has endured, turning him into a cruel individual. He may serve as an accomplice, but gaining his loyalty requires great effort. He appears to possess a saviour-complex, taking great risks to rescue those he doesn't know while still remaining wary of those he saves. This paradoxical aspect of his character intrigued me greatly. Psychosis:

I will keep things simple. When I help you, you return the favor. Don't expect anything like friendship from me. Second, a word of advice: the world is a cold place. You must either adapt to its cruelty or die fighting against it. I know firsthand. Why do I bother saving people? It's ridiculous when I think about it, but no matter how hard I try.. I just move on my own.

addons.title: Status: Psion
addons.text: - Notice-me-not: Can go unnoticed by everything for 7 mins. - Eldritch blast: Can burn through stone, has rapid-fire variant. - Oracle: Can sense any danger within range of 12 meters. - Construct: Can make weapons, tools and shields.

objects.title: Nephilim
objects.text:
A young woman who was deeply interested and captivated by supernatural and mystical phenomena, was initially filled with joy when she realized that these extraordinary occurrences were indeed happening in the world. However, her joy turned to sorrow when her beloved grandmother got corrupted, transformed into a sentient forest, and transformed by the very powers she had admired. She now desires to develop her skills to put an end to her grandmother's suffering. Her "Mecha" ability takes the form of a hooded entity wielding two scythes, perfectly suited for some heavy-duty gardening work. Psychosis:

Hey there! How are you? Do you have any special powers? Can I see them? Let's compare! Oh, and if you're ever in a tight spot, just let ol' reliable me know. I'll swoop in and take care of whatever causing you trouble. And don't forget, if you're hungry, I've got some mean cookies that my dad used to say were the best. My.. Grandma? It's none of your business.

addons.title: Status: 'Normal'
addons.text: - Mecha: A 18 meter tall body, Wields 2 scythes that can rip through steel, Can function separate from core body - Levitation: Can hover upto 10 meter above the ground. - Mist: Can produce thick mist that hinders vision upto 40 meters

objects.title: Amanda Rose
objects.text:
Amanda is merely a child, left alone in a dangerous world filled with wicked people, Her parents no longer in the picture. In terms of combat or survival skills, she possesses few, if any. Her only unique abilities are the ability to see in the dark and discerning lies. Her parents had the foresight to prepare an underground bunker, stocked with valuable resources like medicine, canned food to last a year for a dozen people, and survival manuals. Amanda resides in the bunker alone, seeking comfort in the company of her stuffed animal companion, Mr. Bear. Psychosis:

Who's there? Back off, I'm wharning you! M-My parents? They... They went to the supermarket. They'll be back soon. Really! So don't even think about trying anything! I swear I'm not lying! They said they would return. They're just stuck in traffic. T-They'll come home soon, We will hug each other and we'll have a nice dinner and- I miss Mommy *sniff*

addons.title: Status: Weak 'Normal'
addons.text: - Night soul: Can perfectly see and navigate in dark, her steps make no sound in it either. - Detection: She can sense when someone is being dishonest, can work on indirect sources like videos too.

objects.title: Chavez Reyes
objects.text:
Chavez, a man whose inflated ego is only rivaled by his remarkable abilities. Known for hunting fearsome creatures from across the world, he sees this new apocalyptic landscape as simply another opportunity to hunt. To date, he has the unique distinction of vanquishing three formidable Ascended monsters in the span of a single month. A feat that would warrant admiration if not for his less-than-admirable personality, For He is the very man who previously dated the woman Lilith once was, The one to break her. He can keep you safe, If you're willing to endure his taunts. Psychosis:

Ah, what's this? You're looking for a strong and capable protector, eh? Lucky you, you're in the presence of a real man! You know, I'm very generous, almost too goodhearted, really. Can't let pathetic little worms like you meet your demise alone. I'll take you under my wing. But don't get it twisted. This ain't gonna be some equal partnership. I'm the one in charge here. Your place? It's below mine.

addons.title: Status: 'Normal'
addons.text: - Anchor: Can shut down any supernatural abilities within a radius of 25 meters, Even affects Ascended ones, can be kept up for 20 mins with a 12 min cool down. - Gun: He has a gun, will never hesitate to shoot a living soul.

objects.title: Dr. Robert V
objects.text:
Robert, a renowned surgeon, had everything a man could wish for - wealth and luxuries, All he used to donate away to help those in need. Imagine his surprise when he woke up one day to find a paw where his hand should be, whiskers in place of his majestic mustache. The esteemed Robert V had been transformed into a cat, but not just any cat - a supernatural one. If that wasn't enough, The World went mad, normalcy snatched from all, it would have been easy to be selfish. But Robert wasn't like that, He wanted to reach out a helping hand to those in need and so, he founded one of the major factions. Psychosis:

My dear child, I know this situation is difficult, and you might be feeling anger, even rage. But before you do something that can't be taken back, remember… every person you see was once someone's child, they had parents who loved them, and they too have lost their families. I don't care if you take me as a companion. But please, be someone who your parents could be proud of.

addons.title: Status:  Host
addons.text: - Eternal: Robert can no longer age, can only be killed via violence - Combustion: Can generate intense flames and launch it upto 9m. - Polarity: Can change his magnetic alignment for various effects. - Undying: Can regenerate from any damage in a day.

objects.title: Karalea
objects.text:
Meet Karalea, or as she's commonly known, "The Monster Girl." She's one of the more active members of the Inhuman faction. She fervently believes that empowered beings represent the next step in evolution, and as such, takes it upon herself to eliminate any individuals who haven't developed any powers, a task she believes helps to improve the genetic pool. Her manifestation, "Beast," requires an animal nearby to activate, but she has cleverly circumvented this limitation by creating a cloak made entirely of wolf skin, effectively allowing her to trigger her powers at will. Psychosis:

You.. You are one of the chosen ones, good, It would've been a shame to kill another. Why am I killing normal humans? What is normal about them? They are bugs, lower than cockroaches, clinging onto those better than them to survive. I'm not in the wrong here, I'm doing everyone a favor, They should devote their pitiful lives into serving us, those who deserve it.

addons.title: Status: Host
addons.text: - Beast: Normally needs animal to be used, She can trigger it at will, Physically the strongest here. - Shockwave: Compliments her punches, Can shatter entire houses. - Bullets: Can launch 20 projectiles at once, cool down of 2 mins

objects.title: -Unknown-
objects.text:
This woman's amnesia renders her incapable of recalling any details about her life prior to the day of the contact. She just recently awoke in an abandoned hospital, left to fend for herself. Despite her limited social aptitude, she possesses innate skill in wielding her eldritch abilities. She can access the Limbo through any reflective surface, making her an excellent scout and scavenger. However, there is a strange phenomenon surrounding her. Her reflection doesn't seem to match her movements as if almost independent of her, and on multiple occasions, it appears to directly stare at you. Psychosis:

... We haven't crossed paths before all this, right? I can't remember anything about my... life. The outside world... What exactly happened? *Mirror behind her cracks* Sh-Shush... Don't pay attention to... to Cyn... I mean, the mirror. Don't look into the mirror. It's a... a bad place.

addons.title: Status: Psion
addons.text: - Limbo: Can access Limbo, And later appear out of any mirror in range of 15 miles. - Psychokinesis: Can affect upto 7 Tons in a range of 23m, Only affects 3 targets at once.

objects.title: Rory Carbone
objects.text:
Rory is an anomaly among the empowered ones. He possesses a separate form, or rather an entity named 'Morningstar.' This entity embodies all of his eldritch traits, giving him access to them only when transformed. Morningstar is a humanoid figure with horns and glowing eyes, surrounded by flames that he commands. The transformation to Morningstar occurs only in times of dire need or danger, In his base form, he is completely powerless, rendering him vulnerable in his base form. Morning is far more confident and aggressive in comparison to Rory, who is a pacifist. Psychosis:

Uhmm, hello. You're not here to hurt us, are you? No? Thank heavens. You can never be too careful these days. Everyone is on edge. I just hope we can all recover from this... I hope I too can recover from... whatever demon possesses me. I don't like to hurt people, but he does. Morningstar revels in it even.

addons.title: Status: ???
addons.text: - Hellfire: Can generate flames upto 5300 degree Celsius and control existing flame in radius of 30 meters. - Superhuman: Can lift upto 45 Tons with max effort. - Velocity: Can reach speeds upto 180mph in 8 seconds.

objects.title: Benefactor
objects.text:
A mysterious individual, always seen carrying around an umbrella, with a face shrouded in shadows. This entity, known as "Benefactor," is a peculiar one, resembling a human but decidedly not human in nature. Benefactor is driven by curiosity, particularly about your powers, which are apparently exceptional among other powered individuals, whom it regards as mere "worms." It operates on a contract basis, offering esoteric services in exchange for some extremely odd tasks. While the trades are peculiar and unusual, they will not harm you in any form. Psychosis:

objects.title: Angel of Hope
objects.text:
In the terrible nights, And in the haunting days, There's no need to fear, For the angel guides the way. Like his sister, the angel who manifested due to the abundance of power in reality, He too appears, riding a horse, both with glowing eyes and seemingly intangible to the world around them. The angel manifests when someone has misplaced their path, helping those who have lost their way and are desperate to return home. It leads them through the most efficient and safe route back to where they belong. Psychosis:

Do not be afraid. I shall lead thou forth to your sanctuary. Steady your heart, Place your faith in the divine, And allow me to be your guide. I̸̡̛̛̹̋̅̓͂̄̉̈́̎͗̽̓̚͠ ̸̭͔͔̻̙̈͒̏͒̀̔̀̆̽̑̈͜a̸̢̧̼͈̦̳̦͈̠̓̇̍̈̃͑͛́͛̔̈́͒̓̄m̵̬͉̗̳̔͌̂̿̃͌͛̄̊̔̽͛ ̶̛͓͕̙̹͇͕̀̈́̂̿͐̂̊̄ḧ̷̢̨͍̯̩͈̞̭̹̤̞e̵̢̫͕̞͇͙̤͉̠̗̍͑ŗ̴̖̊̄̽̉͂̑̾̍é̷̱̙̱͇͚͇̲͎̘̫͓̠͕͋͋̓̚͜͜͠ ̴̡̢̺̖̱̹̝̻̠͙̘̽͂̑̈́̃̒͋t̸̳̙̖̗̃̈͑̎̈͊̈́̑̈o̷͖̙̕͜

addons.title: Status: ???
addons.text: - Glitch: Passively intangible to everything. - Heal aura: Those who follow him get minor healing, especially on legs. - Mist: Always seen emerging out from fogs.

defaultRowText: This is a row, and inside of it, you can place choices. On both rows and choices Requirements can be placed, which will block a row from being viewed, or make the player unable to select a choice, depending on either Point-types or the Ids of other choices. Point-types can be made in Features then Manage Points. Hovering over buttons will explain what they do. The Design of the project can be changed in 'Modify Design' at the side navigation bar, and private styling for each row can be turned on in the rows Settings. Default text like this can be turned off in Features -> Manage Defaults.
defaultChoiceText: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.
